      <p>
        This university project demonstrates the use of advanced C++ features to create an optimized simulation for Conway's Game of Life. 
        It can accurately run simulations on varying board sizes and search for specific patterns, including spaceships. 
        This codebase has been built from scratch using object-orientation and utilizes many C++ features including operator overloading, templates, threading, and interfaces.
      </p>
